title: Used (The) - Demos from the Basement [neuroxik] RESEED
description:
THE USED - DEMOS FROM THE BASEMENT

**** RESEED ****

General Info
===================================

Sorry about the bad sound quality. Atleast it's bearable, and although I've 
compressed it to 192 kb/sec, there would have been no use in using higher bitrate
because my source sounded like ~96 kb/sec. 

But enjoy, there's some tracks found nowhere else, some remastered on "Maybe Memories" like Zero Mechanism,
and early versions like "A box full of sharp objects". If you're a hardcore The Used Fan, you'll really 
appreciate, and seeing where they've started. This CD is really rare, only 200 copies were printed, 
and as of today (March 19th 2008 [edit: available sources may have changed (03/28/09)]), I haven't found any other *working* torrents out there for this one.

- neuroxik

technical note: writing "the used" in the title truncated it to "theed", so I resorted to writing "Used (the)", but which also happens conveniently (a bit) because the band was simply called "Used" at the time.
